        <author email="rgettman@users.sourceforge.net">Randy Gettman</author>
        <title>Installation</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section id="download" name="Download">
            <p>Download the latest release version of the <a href="http://jagg.sourceforge.net">jAgg</a>
                library from <a href="http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=369830">SourceForge.net</a>.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="installation" name="Installation">
            <p>To use the jAgg library, place the <strong><code>jagg-core</code></strong> jar in
                your classpath.
            </p>
            <p>If you are using Maven 2+, then you may place the following dependency in your pom.xml.
                Since 0.6.0, jAgg has been available in the Maven 2 Central Repository.</p>
<source>
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;net.sf.jagg&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;jagg-core&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;0.7.1&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
</source>
            <p>The jAgg library does not depend on any third-party libraries, but it does rely on
                JUnit 4.8.2 for JUnit test cases when building through Maven.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="buildingFromSource" name="Building from source">
            <p>It is possible to build jAgg directly from its source code, if the latest unreleased
                changes are needed.  Use a Subversion client to get the source code and
                <a href="http://maven.apache.org/">Apache Maven</a> to build it.  Here are the steps:
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>Get the latest jAgg source code from Sourceforge Subversion using the following command:
                    <source>svn co https://jagg.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/jagg/trunk jagg</source>
                </li>
                <li>Run the following Maven command to build jAgg and install it into the local repository:
                    <source>mvn clean install</source>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </body>
</document>
